        </div>
    </header>
    <section class="post-body text">
        Section 51 of the Senior Courts Act 1981 confers discretion on the court in respect of &ldquo;the costs of and incidental to all proceedings&rdquo;. It has long been understood that the reference to costs &ldquo;of and incidental&rdquo; to proceedings covers pre-action costs. A recent decision illustrates how the jurisdiction to award pre-action costs works in practice and highlights the differenc... <a href="/post/2016/05/16/When-is-a-Claimant-liable-for-pre-action-costs">[More]</a>
        
